The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Friday, April 02, 2004  Adderly claims Amberetta Cup 
 BY STAR RACER Vijay SinghC. Alford on Adderly (left) winning the Amberetta Cup from Signal Tap and Say It Loud at the RCTC on Thursday. Pictures by Kishor Roychowdhury Calcutta: Displaying no discomfiture following his long abscence from the race track, the Vijay Singh-trained Adderly recorded his third straight victory to claim the Amberetta Cup on Thursday. C. Alford partnred the 2-1 favourite.				 										The afternoon, for a change, was, dominated by fancied winners after punters had taken a beating for successive two meetings last week. Even the Bookmakers Cup, which is known as a burial ground for favourites, was lifted by a heavily fancied Tagged For Terror from trainer Daniel Davids yard. Amyn Merchant partnered the 6-10 hot-favourite to an easy victory.				 										RESULTS				 										1. Desert Night Handicap 1,400m: (1-2-3-4) Way To The Stars (Domingo) 1; Mythical Star (Merchant) 2; Kargil Soldier (Rutherford) 3; Regal Rocket (Smith) 4. Won by: 1-3/4; 6; Nk; (1-26.5). Tote: Win Rs 26; Place: 16; 20; Quinella: 39; Shp: 48; Tanala: 146. Fav: Way To The Stars (1). Winner trained by J. Stephens.				 										2. Bookmakers Association Cup 1,200m: (4-7-5-1) Tagged For Terror (Merchant) 1; Forest Ridge (Gajender) 2; Mesopotamia (Salim) 3; Advancer (J. Gurang) 4. Won by: 3; 5; 1/2; (1-13.4). Tote: Win Rs 16; Place: 10; 16; 34; Quinella: 36; Shp: 55; Tanala: 385. Fav: Tagged For Terror (4). Winner trained by Daniel D.				 										3. Aada-Rossa Cup 1,100m: (4-7-2-5) Annabee (C. Alford) 1; Secret Prospector (Merchant) 2; Mayavi (A. P. Singh) 3; Beyond The Clouds (Salim) 4. Won by: 1-3/4; 6; 3; (1-8.1). Tote: Win Rs 25; Place: 12; 12; 22; Quinella: 21; Shp: 28; Tanala: 183. Fav: Secret Prospector (7). Winner trained by Vijay S.				 										4. Gabarnac Handicap 1,100m: (4-7-5-2) Stimulated (Gajender) 1; Asprey (M. Reuben) 2; Star Cutter (A. P. Singh) 3; Jaannisar (Maseyk) 4. Won by: 1/2; 1-1/2; 1; (1-7.3). Tote: Win Rs 29; Place: 14; 14; 27; Quinella: 41; Shp: 49; Tanala: 629. Fav: Stimulated (4). Winner trained by Daniel D. (Note: The winner survived an objection lodged by the rider of the second placed horse).				 										5. Amberetta Cup 1,400m: (3-2-1-5) Adderly (C. Alford) 1; Signal Tap (Gajender) 2; Say It Loud (Surender) 3; Lucifer (Upadhya) 4. Won by: 1/2; 1/2; 1-1/2; (1-25.9). Tote: Win Rs 28; Place: 16; 20; 21; Quinella: 89; Shp: 87; Tanala: 574. Fav: Adderly (3). Winner trained by Vijay S.				 										6. Lord Of Clyde Handicap 1,100m: (1-7-2-3) Perfect Vision (Domingo) 1; Great View (Kujur) 2; Land Of Fantasy (Merchant) 3; Gul (Surender) 4. Won by: 3-1/2; Hd; 2-1/2; (1-7.4). Tote: Win Rs 39; Place: 15; 35; 14; Quinella: 237; Shp: 92; Tanala: 1,134. Fav: Land Of Fantasy (2). Winner trained by Bath.				 										Jackpot: Rs 1,156; (C) Rs 102.				 										Treble: (i) Rs 119; (ii) Rs 321.
